# List of configuration data for FT process in CBOR structures
## List of  config parameters
* All listed names here that appear after <span style="color:red">"Name"</span> are reserved.
* <span style="color:red">"Type"</span> field defines special type of parameter (date, URL, number and etc.)
When the parameter's data is bytes array or string,we do not define its type.
* All data including ACL data is dummy in this example.
* ACL data is redundant for parameters that will not be saved in file system.
* AccountID is an optional parameter.
```css
  "ConfigParams" [
                 [ 
			  {"Name":"SchemeVersion"},
			  {"Type":"VerNumber"},
			  {"Data":"0.0.1"}],
                 [
			  {"Name":"RTCTime"},
			  {"Type":"date"},
			  {"Data":1345618496346},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],
                 [
			  {"Name":"Entropy"},
			  {"Data":0x04182D0E4BC64A1A133B93D0280A7268D3839A16D77728E2B3B526C6B97A9667}],
                 [
			  {"Name":"EndpointName"},
			  {"Data":"Endpoint_name"},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],
                 [
			  {"Name":"AccountID"},
			  {"Data":15842342139673485},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],
                 [
			  {"Name":"ManfName"},
			  {"Data":"Manufacturer_name"},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],	
                 [
			  {"Name":"DevType"},
			  {"Data":"Device_type"},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],	
                 [
			  {"Name":"ModelNum"},
			  {"Data":0x34ab3219},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],	
                  [
			  {"Name":"DevSerialNum"},
			  {"Data":0x93ad9b37},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],	
                  [
			  {"Name":"MemorySize"},
			  {"Type":"Number"},
			  {"Data":0x00000400},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],				  
                 ]
```
## List of keys
* All listed names here that appear after <span style="color:red">"Name"</span> are reserved.
* <span style="color:red">"Type"</span> field defines crypto scheme and key type (private or public).
* <span style="color:red">"Format"</span> field values - pem or der.
* All data including ACL data is dummy in this example.
```css

	"Keys":  [
	         [	
			  {"Name":"BtsDTLSDevice"},
			  {"Type": "ECCPrivate"},
			  {"Format":"der"},
			  {"Data":0x0C182D0E4BC63A1A136593D0280A7268D3839A16D77728E2B3B526C6B97A90CB},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],
	         [	
			  {"Name":"E2EDevice"},
			  {"Type": "ECCPrivate"},
			  {"Format":"der"},
			  {"Data":0x0C182D0E4BC63A1A136593D0280A7268D3839A16D77728E2B3B526C6B97A90CB},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}],
	         [	
			  {"Name":"LWM2MDevice"},
			  {"Type": "ECCPrivate"},
			  {"Format":"pem"},
			  {"Data":0x0C182D0E4BC63A1A136593D0280A7268D3839A16D77728E2B3B526C6B97A90CB},
			  {"ACL":0x3423423423cd132a231b4591d2340d234bc321a}]

	         ]
```

## List of CSRs
* All listed names here that appear after <span style="color:red">"Name"</span> are reserved.
* <span style="color:red">"Format"</span> field values - pem or der.
* CSRs data is not saved in file system and for this reason we don't need ACLs.
